Language course intended for students of the Administration of Social Work specialisation for the acquisition of specialised terminology. The students will acquire the necessary language skills and knowledge for professional work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Acquisition of professional vocabulary and development of professional literacy in students as (future) social workers. The purpose of the course is to provide students with knowledge of professional vocabulary in Russian and to teach them to use it in various situations necessary for working with different clients and in different social institutions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  Can express themselves, as a (future) social worker, in professional Russian, communicate with clients of social institutions in Russian, can use terms related to social work and knows relevant vocabulary.
